{"title_page": "Marzia Kjellberg", "text_new": "{{Redirect|Marzia}}\n{{short description|Italian Internet personality and fashion designer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Marzia Kjellberg\n| image              = Marzia Bisognin on Instagram.jpg\n| caption            = Kjellberg in 2014\n| birth_name         = Marzia Bisognin\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1992|10|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Arzignano]], Italy\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = Italian\n| residence          = [[Brighton]], England\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* [[Internet personality]]\n* [[fashion designer]]\n* [[businessperson]]\n}}\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[PewDiePie|Felix Kjellberg]]|2019}}\n| website            = {{URL|https://ma\u00ec.com/}}\n| module             = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| pseudonym            = CutiePieMarzia\n| channel_direct_url   = user/CutiePieMarzia\n| channel_display_name = Marzia\n| years_active         = 2012\u20132018\n| genre                = {{flatlist|\n* [[Vlog]]\n* [[fashion]]\n* [[Beauty YouTubers|beauty]]\n* [[Travel]]\n* [[Do it yourself|DIY]]\n* [[popular culture]]\n* [[Haul video|shopping]]\n* [[Video game culture|gaming]]\n}}\n| subscribers          = 7.6 million<!--please update date in stats_update field when you update this--> <!--do not add the date here as that is already at the bottom of the infobox-->\n| views                = 23.0 million<!--please update date in stats_update field when you update this--> <!--do not add the date here as that is already at the bottom of the infobox-->\n| network              = [[Disney Digital Network]]\n| associated_acts      = {{flatlist|\n* [[PewDiePie]]\n* [[Bunny Meyer]]\n* [[PJ Liguori]]\n}}\n| silver_year          = 2012\n| gold_year            = 2013\n| silver_button        = yes\n| gold_button          = yes\n| stats_update         = 6 April 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Marzia Kjellberg'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/itsmarziapie/|title=Marzia Kjellberg (@itsmarziapie) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|work=itsmarziapie|publisher=[[Instagram]]|language=en|access-date=21 August 2019}}</ref> ({{nee}} '''Bisognin''';{{efn|Italian: {{IPA-it|\u02c8martsja bizo\u0272\u02c8\u0272in|}}, Venetian: {{IPA-vec|bizo\u02c8\u0272i\u014b|}}.}} born 21 October 1992) is an Italian [[Internet personality]], [[fashion design]]er, and businesswoman. Known for her videos on her now-inactive [[YouTube]] channel, Kjellberg has also ventured into writing, fashion designing, and business.\n\n==Career==\n===YouTube===\nKjellberg registered her ''CutiePieMarzia'' YouTube channel on 16 January 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/CutiePieMarzia/about|title=Marzia|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=22 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924051028/https://www.youtube.com/user/CutiePieMarzia/about|archive-date=24 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Kjellberg's videos on YouTube focused on fashion, beauty, makeup, [[Do it yourself|DIY]], books, movies, [[vlogs]], [[haul video|haul]], and [[video gaming]].<ref name=\"X2013\">{{cite web|last=X |first=Ashleigh |url=http://www.magazinesandmodels.com/2013/06/marzia-bisognin-interview.html |title=Marzia Bisognin Interview |website=Magazines and Models |date=22 June 2013 |accessdate=22 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130724052005/http://www.magazinesandmodels.com/2013/06/marzia-bisognin-interview.html |archive-date=24 July 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Knorr|first=Caroline|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/common-sense-media/what-kids-are-really-watc_b_9197366.html|title=What Kids Are Really Watching on YouTube|work=Huffington Post|date=11 February 2016|accessdate=11 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424040708/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/common-sense-media/what-kids-are-really-watc_b_9197366.html|archive-date=24 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Although Italian, Kjellberg spoke English in her videos in order to increase her target audience. Kjellberg was signed to [[Maker Studios]]' sub-[[multi-channel network|network]], The Platform.<ref name=\"Spangler2013\">{{cite magazine|last=Spangler|first=Todd|url=https://variety.com/2013/digital/news/pewdiepie-captures-youtube-no-1-channel-spot-topping-justin-bieber-and-taylor-swift-1200579720/|title=PewDiePie Captures YouTube No. 1 Channel Spot, Topping Justin Bieber and Taylor Swift|magazine=Variety|date=16 August 2013|accessdate=27 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612195731/http://variety.com/2013/digital/news/pewdiepie-captures-youtube-no-1-channel-spot-topping-justin-bieber-and-taylor-swift-1200579720/|archive-date=12 June 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Kjellberg's YouTube channel was one of the most popular in the [[beauty YouTuber|beauty and makeup genre]]. In May 2014, ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' reported that it attracts over 16 million viewers each month.<ref name=\"Shields2014a\">{{cite web|last=Shields|first=Mike|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2014/05/08/beauty-is-a-monster-category-on-youtube-and-its-still-growing/|title=Beauty is a Monster Category on YouTube, and it's Still Growing|work=The Wall Street Journal|department=CMO Today|date=8 May 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924141135/http://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2014/05/08/beauty-is-a-monster-category-on-youtube-and-its-still-growing/|archive-date=24 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Additionally, Kjellberg's channel is the most subscribed Italian YouTube channel.<ref name=\"Particelli2014\">{{cite web|last=Particelli|first=Daniele|url=http://www.downloadblog.it/post/115774/i-5-canali-italiani-piu-seguiti-su-youtube|title=I 5 canali italiani pi\u00f9 seguiti su YouTube|website=Blogo|publisher=Triboo Media|date=18 September 2014|accessdate=29 September 2014|language=Italian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006070041/http://www.downloadblog.it/post/115774/i-5-canali-italiani-piu-seguiti-su-youtube|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Sanna2014\">{{cite web|last=Sanna|first=Umberto|url=http://www.tecnocino.it/2014/09/articolo/i-5-canali-youtube-italiani-piu-seguiti/54461/|title=I 5 canali Youtube italiani pi\u00f9 seguiti|website=Tecnocino|publisher=NanoPress|date=22 September 2014|accessdate=29 September 2014|language=Italian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929044742/http://www.tecnocino.it/2014/09/articolo/i-5-canali-youtube-italiani-piu-seguiti/54461/|archive-date=29 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> The demographics of Kjellberg's viewers have been reported to be females aged 13\u201324, who use Kjellberg's videos as a reference.<ref name=\"Mutterle2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgiornaledivicenza.it/stories/dalla_home/626340_lo_stile_di_marzia_conquista_youtube_e_due_milioni_di_fan/|title=Lo stile di Marzia conquista YouTube e due milioni di fan|last=Mutterle|first=Paolo|date=21 January 2014|website=Il Giornale Di Vicenza|publisher=Societ\u00e0 Athesis|location=Verona, Italy|language=Italian|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010170554/http://www.ilgiornaledivicenza.it/stories/dalla_home/626340_lo_stile_di_marzia_conquista_youtube_e_due_milioni_di_fan/|archive-date=10 October 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014}}</ref> Kjellberg refers to her fans as \"Marzipans\".<ref name=\"Demirgian2015\">{{cite web|last = Demirgian|first = Francesca|url = http://velvetstyle.it/2015/06/09/cutiepiemarzia-marzia-bisognin-youtube-tutorial-moda-bellezza/|title = CutiePieMarzia, chi \u00e8 la fashion youtuber che fa impazzire le giovanissime [VIDEO]|website=Velvet Style|publisher=MetUp|date = 9 June 2015|accessdate = 22 June 2015|language = Italian|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150614062728/http://velvetstyle.it/2015/06/09/cutiepiemarzia-marzia-bisognin-youtube-tutorial-moda-bellezza/|archive-date = 14 June 2015|url-status=live|df = dmy-all}}</ref> In 2014, Kjellberg and then-boyfriend Felix Kjellberg were part of an online marketing campaign for the horror film, ''[[As Above, So Below (film)|As Above, So Below]]''.<ref name=\"Bauckhage2014\">{{cite magazine|last=Bauckhage|first=Tobias|url=https://variety.com/2014/digital/news/social-media-buzz-november-man-labors-to-overcome-as-above-so-below-1201294050/|title=Social Media Buzz: 'November Man' Labors to Overcome 'As Above, So Below'|magazine=Variety|date=29 August 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010190324/http://variety.com/2014/digital/news/social-media-buzz-november-man-labors-to-overcome-as-above-so-below-1201294050/|archive-date=10 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> While Felix's videos for the campaign involved gaming-related topics, Marzia's videos centered around a travel vlog angle of the couple's trip to Paris.<ref name=\"Coyle2014\">{{cite web|last=Coyle|first=Meghan|url=http://www.etcentric.org/youtube-power-couple-produces-miniseries-for-horror-movie/|title=YouTube Power Couple Produces Miniseries for Horror Movie|website=ET Centric|publisher=Entertainment Technology Center|date=2 September 2014|accessdate=29 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006202743/http://www.etcentric.org/youtube-power-couple-produces-miniseries-for-horror-movie/|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Similarly, [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] had Marzia, among others, promote their new TV series, ''[[Selfie (TV series)|Selfie]]'' via a YouTube marketing campaign.<ref name=\"Poggi2014\">{{cite web|last=Poggi|first=Jeanine|url=http://adage.com/article/media/tv-networks-promote-shows-youtube/295313/|title=ABC Revamps YouTube Marketing to Better Reach Digital Viewers|website=Advertising Age|date=8 October 2014|accessdate=10 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010132115/http://adage.com/article/media/tv-networks-promote-shows-youtube/295313/|archive-date=10 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 October 2018, Kjellberg uploaded a video to her channel announcing her retirement from her YouTube career.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/10/22/18009010/youtuber-marzia-bisognin-quits-mental-health-youtube|title=YouTuber Marzia Calls It Quits in a Personal Video About Mental Health|last=Farokhmanesh|first=Megan|date=22 October 2018|website=The Verge|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112123043/https://www.theverge.com/2018/10/22/18009010/youtuber-marzia-bisognin-quits-mental-health-youtube|archive-date=12 January 2019|access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref> In the video she mentioned that at a point during her YouTube career, focusing on the website kept her in a bubble that negatively affected her mental health, although she resolved to reach out to others. She ended her video explaining that she was ready for \"something new in [her] life.\" After she uploaded her final vlog, as she decided to remove her videos; she left a comment on the vlog stating, \"Having videos up, after making this decision, would have seemed like taking a step back. I've selected a few that I really liked, which I'm going to leave for a bit&nbsp;\u2013 for the 'adjustment' period&nbsp;\u2013 but taking my videos down, in my mind, needed to be done.\"<ref name=\"Bisognin2018\">{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KvVOf7Mx5iM|title=Goodbye Youtube.|date=22 October 2018|last=Bisognin|first=Marzia|accessdate=25 October 2018|work=Marzia|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025012922/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KvVOf7Mx5iM|archive-date=25 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Shortly before her announcement, her YouTube channel had accumulated over 128 million video views and just under 7.5 million subscribers.<ref name=\"SocialBladeA\">{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/cutiepiemarzia|title=Marzia YouTube channel statistics (12\u201325 October 2018 archive)|publisher=[[Social Blade]]|date=25 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025050021/https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/cutiepiemarzia|archive-date=25 October 2018}}</ref> Her channel's video views previously peaked in August 2017, at around 570 million.<ref name=\"SocialBladeB\">{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/cutiepiemarzia|title=Cutiepiemarzia Monthly YouTube statistics (8 June-8 July 2018 archive)|publisher=[[Social Blade]]|date=8 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707115856/https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/cutiepiemarzia/monthly|archive-date=8 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nAside from creating content on her own channel, Kjellberg has been a voice actress in various animated web series. She voiced Carrie the Carrot in ''Oscar's Hotel for Fantastical Creatures''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Pearce|first=Tilly|url=http://teneightymagazine.com/2015/08/16/new-oscars-hotel-characters-announced-at-summer-in-the-city-2015/|title=New Oscar's Hotel Characters Announced at Summer in the City 2015|website=TenEighty|date=16 August 2015|accessdate=11 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313215408/http://teneightymagazine.com/2015/08/16/new-oscars-hotel-characters-announced-at-summer-in-the-city-2015/|archive-date=13 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Kjellberg also voiced the character Maya, based on her own dog, in a six-episode animated web series titled ''Pugatory''.<ref name=\"Rody2015\">{{cite web|last=Rody-Mantha|first=Bree|url=http://streamdaily.tv/2015/10/28/new-series-pugatory-features-the-voice-talent-of-pewdiepie/|title=New series Pugatory features the voice talent of PewDiePie|website=StreamDaily|publisher=Brunico Communications|date=28 October 2015|accessdate=11 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160423091425/http://streamdaily.tv/2015/10/28/new-series-pugatory-features-the-voice-talent-of-pewdiepie/|archive-date=23 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Fashion and design===\nKjellberg's channel's success allowed her to start designing her own clothing.<ref name=\"Trowbridge2015\">{{cite magazine|last=Trowbridge|first=Cecily|url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/59431-5-inspiring-youtubers-who-prove-coupledom-doesnt-define-you-because-you-may-need-a-reminder-on|title=5 Inspiring YouTubers Who Prove Coupledom Doesn't Define You (Because You May Need A Reminder on Valentine's Day)|magazine=Bustle|date=20 January 2015|accessdate=22 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150622220307/http://www.bustle.com/articles/59431-5-inspiring-youtubers-who-prove-coupledom-doesnt-define-you-because-you-may-need-a-reminder-on|archive-date=22 June 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Since March 2015, Kjellberg has launched several lines of fashion and design merchandise including nail polish shade, home decor products, and most notably clothing.<ref name=\"Gutelle2018\">\n{{cite web|last=Gutelle|first=Sam|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/06/26/marzia-fashion-line-linee/|title=YouTube Star Marzia Celebrates Summer With Launch Of Her Latest Fashion Line|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=26 June 2018|accessdate=31 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801044450/https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/06/26/marzia-fashion-line-linee/|archive-date=1 August 2018|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Her clothing lines are sold through her online store.\n\nIn 2016, she designed \"Daisy\" shoes through Project Shoe.<ref>{{cite web|last=Olivia|first=Sage|url=https://sageolivia.com/2014/07/27/daisy-by-marzia/|title=\"Daisy\" by Marzia|work=Sage Olivia|date=27 July 2014|accessdate=21 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222114513/https://sageolivia.com/2014/07/27/daisy-by-marzia/|archive-date=22 February 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> That July, she launched a product line with Zoya, a nail polish brand.<ref name=\"Gutelle2016\">{{cite web|last=Gutelle|first=Sam|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2016/07/07/cutie-pie-marzia-bisognin-nail-polish-zoya/|title=YouTube Star Cutie Pie Marzia Launches Her Own Shade Of Nail Polish|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=7 July 2016|accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref> In June 2017, Kjellberg launched Lemon, a clothing line paired with a fragrance.<ref name=\"Klein2017\">{{cite web|last=Klein|first=Jessica|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/06/23/youtube-star-marzia-bisognin-marziapie-fashion-line-scent-trunk/|title=YouTube Star MarziaPie Launches Fashion Line with Scent Trunk|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=23 June 2017|accessdate=14 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190114191904/https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/06/23/youtube-star-marzia-bisognin-marziapie-fashion-line-scent-trunk/|archive-date=14 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn a piece about fashion lines created by YouTube personalities, ''[[Tubefilter]]'' cited comments from Michael Fink, the dean of the School of Fashion at [[Savannah College of Art and Design]], as well as celebrity stylist Allison Calhoun. Kjellberg's \"Amore\" clothing line was positively received by Fink, who stated \"the gold zipper and heart applique of this skirt are right on trend, yet the A-line silhouette is timeless. You can't go wrong with this piece.\"<ref name=\"Weiss2018\">{{cite web|last=Weiss|first=Jeff|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/02/28/fashion-experts-review-youtuber-collections/|title=From Faze Banks To Hila Klein, We Asked Experts To Review Fashion Lines From YouTube Stars|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=28 February 2018|accessdate=31 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801044452/https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/02/28/fashion-experts-review-youtuber-collections/|archive-date=1 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Calhoun opined that \"I'm personally not crazy about the patterns, colors, or cuts but I definitely can see the customer who might be. I also want to applaud Marzia and her designs for not being as topical as the others. It seems like she's making clothes that she wants to wear without a ton of inspiration from the outside world.\"<ref name=\"Weiss2018\" />\n\nOn 1 July 2018, Kjellberg launched Ma\u00ec, a jewellery, pottery, and home decor brand.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bisognin|first=Marzia|url=https://marziaslife.com/2018/07/01/mai/|title=Ma\u00ec|work=Marzia's Life|date=1 July 2018|accessdate=12 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712183132/https://marziaslife.com/2018/07/01/mai/|archive-date=12 July 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> The Ma\u00ec ceramic accents are handcrafted by Kjellberg out of her UK-based pottery studio.<ref name=\"Barandy2019\">{{cite web|last=Barandy|first=Kat|url=https://www.designboom.com/art/mai-accents-marzia-bisognin-ceramics-03-23-19/|title=marzia bisognin crafts gang of pottery creatures with latest collection, ma\u00ec accents|work=[[designboom]]|date=23 February 2019|accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref> She maintains that brand along with Tsuki Market, a unisex clothing and homeware brand that she owns with husband [[PewDiePie|Felix Kjellberg]].<ref name=\"Weiss2019\">{{cite web|last=Weiss|first=Geoff|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2019/03/04/marzia-bisgonon-feels-good-about-quitting-youtube/|title=Marzia Bisgonin Says She \"Feels Good\" About Quitting YouTube, After Adjustment Period|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=4 March 2019|accessdate=22 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322231837/https://www.tubefilter.com/2019/03/04/marzia-bisgonon-feels-good-about-quitting-youtube/|archive-date=22 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Other ventures===\nIn January 2015, Kjellberg published a young adult fantasy/horror novel.<ref name=\"Dream House\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27173614-dream-house|title=Dream House|publisher=Goodreads}}</ref> The Italian version was published under the title ''La Casa Dei Sogni'' while the English version was published as ''Dream House: A Novel by CutiePieMarzia''.<ref name=\"Bisognin\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iphvBgAAQBAJ|title=Dream House|last=Bisognin|first=Marzia \"CutiePie\"|date=29 January 2015|publisher=Newton Compton Editori|isbn=9788854179660|language=it|access-date=17 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160515052858/https://books.google.com/books?id=iphvBgAAQBAJ|archive-date=15 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKjellberg was born on 21 October 1992 in [[Arzignano]], located in the [[Province of Vicenza]], Italy.<ref name=\"Mutterle2014\" />\n\nShe was introduced to her husband, Felix Kjellberg, better known online as [[PewDiePie]], by her friend Daizo who recommended that she watch \"this idiot playing video games\".<ref name=\"BAA2015\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2920089/The-King-YouTube-25-year-old-makes-2-6m-year-just-playing-computer-games-Brighton-flat-shares-model-girlfriend-yes-did-meet-internet.html|title=The King of YouTube: How 25-year-old makes \u00a32.6m a year just from playing computer games in Brighton flat he shares with girlfriend (and yes, they did meet over the internet)|last1=Boyle|first1=Sian|date=23 January 2015|newspaper=The Daily Mail|accessdate=22 June 2015|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.is/20150218084732/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2920089/The-King-YouTube-25-year-old-makes-2-6m-year-just-playing-computer-games-Brighton-flat-shares-model-girlfriend-yes-did-meet-internet.html|archive-date=18 February 2015|last2=Andersson|first2=Ulf|last3=Akbar|first3=Jay}}</ref> She began dating Kjellberg in 2011, after e-mailing him and stating that she found his videos funny.<ref name=\"Ryall2014\">{{cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2014/06/20/meet-the-guy-making-4m-a-year-on-youtube/|title=Meet the guy making $4M a year on YouTube|last=Ryall|first=Jenni|date=20 June 2014|newspaper=New York Post|accessdate=29 September 2014|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141005001905/http://nypost.com/2014/06/20/meet-the-guy-making-4m-a-year-on-youtube/|archive-date=5 October 2014}}</ref> She then moved to [[Sweden]], to live with him that October. They later moved to her native Italy, before settling together in [[Brighton]], England.<ref name=\"Expressen1\">{{cite news|url=http://bloggar.expressen.se/lars/2012/07/pewdiepie-rules-one-million-subscribers/|title=COLUMN Pewdiepie rules, now one million subscribers|last=Lindstrom|first=Lars|date=13 July 2012|newspaper=Expressen|accessdate=22 September 2014|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923060946/http://bloggar.expressen.se/lars/2012/07/pewdiepie-rules-one-million-subscribers/|archive-date=23 September 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"theargus\">{{cite web|url=http://www.theargus.co.uk/news/10796646.Brighton_YouTube_sensation_has_more_subscribers_than_Justin_Bieber/|title=Brighton YouTube sensation has more subscribers than Justin Bieber|last=Scott-Delany|first=Finn|date=9 November 2013|website=The Argus|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006071824/http://www.theargus.co.uk/news/10796646.Brighton_YouTube_sensation_has_more_subscribers_than_Justin_Bieber/|archive-date=6 October 2014|accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"UKresidence\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MarziaPie/status/403534925350973440|title=Still in Brighton...|last=Bisognin|first=Marzia|date=21 November 2013|work=MarziaPie|publisher=Twitter|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201175245/https://twitter.com/MarziaPie/status/403534925350973440|archive-date=1 February 2015|accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref> The couple live with their two [[pug]]s, Edgar and Maya,<ref name=\"Lindgvist2014\">{{cite news|url=http://www.gp.se/kulturnoje/1.2511893-pewdiepie-talar-ut-i-unik-intervju|title=Pewdiepie talar ut i unik intervju|last=Lindqvist|first=Johan|date=8 October 2014|newspaper=[[G\u00f6teborgs-Posten]]|accessdate=10 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304194754/http://www.gp.se/kulturnoje/1.2511893-pewdiepie-talar-ut-i-unik-intervju|archivedate=4 March 2016|language=Swedish}}</ref> as well as a hedgehog named Dogy. Their relationship has been highlighted by various media outlets,<ref name=\"Shields2014b\">{{cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2014/08/28/youtube-power-couple-pewdiepie-and-cutiepiemarzia-create-miniseries-for-movie-as-above-so-below/|title=YouTube Power Couple PewDiePie and CutiePieMarzia Create Miniseries For Movie \"As Above, So Below\"|last=Shields|first=Mike|date=28 August 2014|newspaper=The Wall Street Journal|accessdate=22 September 2014|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929223437/http://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2014/08/28/youtube-power-couple-pewdiepie-and-cutiepiemarzia-create-miniseries-for-movie-as-above-so-below/|archive-date=29 September 2014|publisher=Dow Jones & Co.|department=CMO Today}}</ref> with ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'' writing that Marzia's \"calm personality balances out [Felix]'s general wackiness.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/digital-culture/pewdiepie-this-profane-bro-you-never-heard-of-is-youtubes-biggest-star/article17079452/|title=PewDiePie: YouTube's biggest star is a profane Swede you've never heard of|last=Woolley|first=Emma|date=25 February 2014|work=The Globe and Mail|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707024510/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/digital-culture/pewdiepie-this-profane-bro-you-never-heard-of-is-youtubes-biggest-star/article17079452/|archive-date=7 July 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014}}</ref> On 27 April 2018, Marzia announced on [[Instagram]] that Felix had proposed to her; on 20 August 2019, the couple announced on social media that they had married.<ref name=Klein2018>{{cite web|last=Klein|first=Jessica|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/04/27/pewdiepie-marzia-proposal/|title=YouTube Star PewDiePie Proposed To Longtime Girlfriend Marzia Bisognin|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=27 April 2018|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Garvey2019\">{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/08/20/entertainment/pewdiepie-and-marzia-bisognin-marry-trnd/index.html|title=PewDiePie and Marzia Bisognin marry after dating for eight years|last=Garvey|first=Marianne|date=20 August 2019|website=[[CNN]]|accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref> The two have a home in Japan together, which was burglarized in late 2019; Kjellberg posted a statement online which included: \"I know it is very materialistic, and should be happy with what I was left/have, but I can't hide the shock and sadness with all being taken away, just like that.\"<ref name=Salo2019>{{cite web|last=Salo|first=Jackie|url=https://nypost.com/2019/12/02/youtube-star-pewdiepie-and-wife-marzia-kjellberg-burglarized-in-home-invasion/|title= YouTube star PewDiePie and wife Marzia Kjellberg burglarized in home invasion |work=[[New York Post]]|date=2 December 2019|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{YouTube|u=CutiePieMarzia|{{PAGENAMEBASE}}}}\n* {{IMDb name|6521291}}\n\n{{PewDiePie}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Fashion|Italy}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kjellberg, Marzia}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Italian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century Italian writers]]\n[[Category:Beauty and makeup YouTubers]]\n[[Category:DIY YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Fashion YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Female YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Italian businesspeople in fashion]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriates in England]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriates in Japan]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriates in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Italian fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Italian horror writers]]\n[[Category:Italian jewellery designers]]\n[[Category:Italian voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Italian women in business]]\n[[Category:Italian women novelists]]\n[[Category:Italian writers of young adult literature]]\n[[Category:Italian YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Lifestyle YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Arzignano]]\n[[Category:Revelmode people]]\n[[Category:Video game commentators]]\n[[Category:Women video bloggers]]\n[[Category:YouTube travel vloggers]]\n[[Category:YouTube vloggers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|Marzia}}\n{{short description|Italian Internet personality and fashion designer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Marzia Kjellberg\n| image              = Marzia Bisognin on Instagram.jpg\n| caption            = Kjellberg in 2014\n| birth_name         = Marzia Bisognin\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1992|10|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Arzignano]], Italy\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = Italian\n| residence          = [[Brighton]], England\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* [[Internet personality]]\n* [[fashion designer]]\n* [[businessperson]]\n}}\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[PewDiePie|Felix Kjellberg]]|2019}}\n| website            = {{URL|https://ma\u00ec.com/}}\n| module             = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| pseudonym            = CutiePieMarzia\n| channel_direct_url   = user/CutiePieMarzia\n| channel_display_name = Marzia\n| years_active         = 2012\u20132018\n| genre                = {{flatlist|\n* [[Vlog]]\n* [[fashion]]\n* [[Beauty YouTubers|beauty]]\n* [[Travel]]\n* [[Do it yourself|DIY]]\n* [[popular culture]]\n* [[Haul video|shopping]]\n* [[Video game culture|gaming]]\n}}\n| subscribers          = 7.6 million<!--please update date in stats_update field when you update this--> <!--do not add the date here as that is already at the bottom of the infobox-->\n| views                = 23.0 million<!--please update date in stats_update field when you update this--> <!--do not add the date here as that is already at the bottom of the infobox-->\n| network              = [[Disney Digital Network]]\n| associated_acts      = {{flatlist|\n* [[PewDiePie]]\n* [[Bunny Meyer]]\n* [[PJ Liguori]]\n}}\n| silver_year          = 2012\n| gold_year            = 2013\n| silver_button        = yes\n| gold_button          = yes\n| stats_update         = 6 April 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Marzia Kjellberg'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/itsmarziapie/|title=Marzia Kjellberg (@itsmarziapie) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|work=itsmarziapie|publisher=[[Instagram]]|language=en|access-date=21 August 2019}}</ref> ({{nee}} '''Bisognin''';{{efn|Italian: {{IPA-it|\u02c8martsja bizo\u0272\u02c8\u0272in|}}, Venetian: {{IPA-vec|bizo\u02c8\u0272i\u014b|}}.}} born 21 October 1992) is an Italian [[Internet personality]], [[fashion design]]er, and businesswoman. Known for her videos on her now-inactive [[YouTube]] channel, Kjellberg has also ventured into writing, fashion designing, and business.\n\n==Career==\n===YouTube===\nKjellberg registered her ''CutiePieMarzia'' YouTube channel on 16 January 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/CutiePieMarzia/about|title=Marzia|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=22 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924051028/https://www.youtube.com/user/CutiePieMarzia/about|archive-date=24 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Kjellberg's videos on YouTube focused on fashion, beauty, makeup, [[Do it yourself|DIY]], books, movies, [[vlogs]], [[haul video|haul]], and [[video gaming]].<ref name=\"X2013\">{{cite web|last=X |first=Ashleigh |url=http://www.magazinesandmodels.com/2013/06/marzia-bisognin-interview.html |title=Marzia Bisognin Interview |website=Magazines and Models |date=22 June 2013 |accessdate=22 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130724052005/http://www.magazinesandmodels.com/2013/06/marzia-bisognin-interview.html |archive-date=24 July 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Knorr|first=Caroline|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/common-sense-media/what-kids-are-really-watc_b_9197366.html|title=What Kids Are Really Watching on YouTube|work=Huffington Post|date=11 February 2016|accessdate=11 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424040708/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/common-sense-media/what-kids-are-really-watc_b_9197366.html|archive-date=24 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Although Italian, Kjellberg spoke English in her videos in order to increase her target audience. Kjellberg was signed to [[Maker Studios]]' sub-[[multi-channel network|network]], The Platform.<ref name=\"Spangler2013\">{{cite magazine|last=Spangler|first=Todd|url=https://variety.com/2013/digital/news/pewdiepie-captures-youtube-no-1-channel-spot-topping-justin-bieber-and-taylor-swift-1200579720/|title=PewDiePie Captures YouTube No. 1 Channel Spot, Topping Justin Bieber and Taylor Swift|magazine=Variety|date=16 August 2013|accessdate=27 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612195731/http://variety.com/2013/digital/news/pewdiepie-captures-youtube-no-1-channel-spot-topping-justin-bieber-and-taylor-swift-1200579720/|archive-date=12 June 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Kjellberg's YouTube channel was one of the most popular in the [[beauty YouTuber|beauty and makeup genre]]. In May 2014, ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' reported that it attracts over 16 million viewers each month.<ref name=\"Shields2014a\">{{cite web|last=Shields|first=Mike|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2014/05/08/beauty-is-a-monster-category-on-youtube-and-its-still-growing/|title=Beauty is a Monster Category on YouTube, and it's Still Growing|work=The Wall Street Journal|department=CMO Today|date=8 May 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924141135/http://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2014/05/08/beauty-is-a-monster-category-on-youtube-and-its-still-growing/|archive-date=24 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Additionally, Kjellberg's channel is the most subscribed Italian YouTube channel.<ref name=\"Particelli2014\">{{cite web|last=Particelli|first=Daniele|url=http://www.downloadblog.it/post/115774/i-5-canali-italiani-piu-seguiti-su-youtube|title=I 5 canali italiani pi\u00f9 seguiti su YouTube|website=Blogo|publisher=Triboo Media|date=18 September 2014|accessdate=29 September 2014|language=Italian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006070041/http://www.downloadblog.it/post/115774/i-5-canali-italiani-piu-seguiti-su-youtube|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Sanna2014\">{{cite web|last=Sanna|first=Umberto|url=http://www.tecnocino.it/2014/09/articolo/i-5-canali-youtube-italiani-piu-seguiti/54461/|title=I 5 canali Youtube italiani pi\u00f9 seguiti|website=Tecnocino|publisher=NanoPress|date=22 September 2014|accessdate=29 September 2014|language=Italian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929044742/http://www.tecnocino.it/2014/09/articolo/i-5-canali-youtube-italiani-piu-seguiti/54461/|archive-date=29 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> The demographics of Kjellberg's viewers have been reported to be females aged 13\u201324, who use Kjellberg's videos as a reference.<ref name=\"Mutterle2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgiornaledivicenza.it/stories/dalla_home/626340_lo_stile_di_marzia_conquista_youtube_e_due_milioni_di_fan/|title=Lo stile di Marzia conquista YouTube e due milioni di fan|last=Mutterle|first=Paolo|date=21 January 2014|website=Il Giornale Di Vicenza|publisher=Societ\u00e0 Athesis|location=Verona, Italy|language=Italian|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010170554/http://www.ilgiornaledivicenza.it/stories/dalla_home/626340_lo_stile_di_marzia_conquista_youtube_e_due_milioni_di_fan/|archive-date=10 October 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014}}</ref> Kjellberg refers to her fans as \"Marzipans\".<ref name=\"Demirgian2015\">{{cite web|last = Demirgian|first = Francesca|url = http://velvetstyle.it/2015/06/09/cutiepiemarzia-marzia-bisognin-youtube-tutorial-moda-bellezza/|title = CutiePieMarzia, chi \u00e8 la fashion youtuber che fa impazzire le giovanissime [VIDEO]|website=Velvet Style|publisher=MetUp|date = 9 June 2015|accessdate = 22 June 2015|language = Italian|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150614062728/http://velvetstyle.it/2015/06/09/cutiepiemarzia-marzia-bisognin-youtube-tutorial-moda-bellezza/|archive-date = 14 June 2015|url-status=live|df = dmy-all}}</ref> In 2014, Kjellberg and then-boyfriend Felix Kjellberg were part of an online marketing campaign for the horror film, ''[[As Above, So Below (film)|As Above, So Below]]''.<ref name=\"Bauckhage2014\">{{cite magazine|last=Bauckhage|first=Tobias|url=https://variety.com/2014/digital/news/social-media-buzz-november-man-labors-to-overcome-as-above-so-below-1201294050/|title=Social Media Buzz: 'November Man' Labors to Overcome 'As Above, So Below'|magazine=Variety|date=29 August 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010190324/http://variety.com/2014/digital/news/social-media-buzz-november-man-labors-to-overcome-as-above-so-below-1201294050/|archive-date=10 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> While Felix's videos for the campaign involved gaming-related topics, Marzia's videos centered around a travel vlog angle of the couple's trip to Paris.<ref name=\"Coyle2014\">{{cite web|last=Coyle|first=Meghan|url=http://www.etcentric.org/youtube-power-couple-produces-miniseries-for-horror-movie/|title=YouTube Power Couple Produces Miniseries for Horror Movie|website=ET Centric|publisher=Entertainment Technology Center|date=2 September 2014|accessdate=29 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006202743/http://www.etcentric.org/youtube-power-couple-produces-miniseries-for-horror-movie/|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Similarly, [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] had Marzia, among others, promote their new TV series, ''[[Selfie (TV series)|Selfie]]'' via a YouTube marketing campaign.<ref name=\"Poggi2014\">{{cite web|last=Poggi|first=Jeanine|url=http://adage.com/article/media/tv-networks-promote-shows-youtube/295313/|title=ABC Revamps YouTube Marketing to Better Reach Digital Viewers|website=Advertising Age|date=8 October 2014|accessdate=10 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010132115/http://adage.com/article/media/tv-networks-promote-shows-youtube/295313/|archive-date=10 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 October 2018, Kjellberg uploaded a video to her channel announcing her retirement from her YouTube career.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/10/22/18009010/youtuber-marzia-bisognin-quits-mental-health-youtube|title=YouTuber Marzia Calls It Quits in a Personal Video About Mental Health|last=Farokhmanesh|first=Megan|date=22 October 2018|website=The Verge|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112123043/https://www.theverge.com/2018/10/22/18009010/youtuber-marzia-bisognin-quits-mental-health-youtube|archive-date=12 January 2019|access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref> In the video she mentioned that at a point during her YouTube career, focusing on the website kept her in a bubble that negatively affected her mental health, although she resolved to reach out to others. She ended her video explaining that she was ready for \"something new in [her] life.\" After she uploaded her final vlog, as she decided to remove her videos; she left a comment on the vlog stating, \"Having videos up, after making this decision, would have seemed like taking a step back. I've selected a few that I really liked, which I'm going to leave for a bit&nbsp;\u2013 for the 'adjustment' period&nbsp;\u2013 but taking my videos down, in my mind, needed to be done.\"<ref name=\"Bisognin2018\">{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KvVOf7Mx5iM|title=Goodbye Youtube.|date=22 October 2018|last=Bisognin|first=Marzia|accessdate=25 October 2018|work=Marzia|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025012922/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KvVOf7Mx5iM|archive-date=25 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Shortly before her announcement, her YouTube channel had accumulated over 128 million video views and just under 7.5 million subscribers.<ref name=\"SocialBladeA\">{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/cutiepiemarzia|title=Marzia YouTube channel statistics (12\u201325 October 2018 archive)|publisher=[[Social Blade]]|date=25 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025050021/https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/cutiepiemarzia|archive-date=25 October 2018}}</ref> Her channel's video views previously peaked in August 2017, at around 570 million.<ref name=\"SocialBladeB\">{{cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/cutiepiemarzia|title=Cutiepiemarzia Monthly YouTube statistics (8 June-8 July 2018 archive)|publisher=[[Social Blade]]|date=8 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707115856/https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/cutiepiemarzia/monthly|archive-date=8 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nAside from creating content on her own channel, Kjellberg has been a voice actress in various animated web series. She voiced Carrie the Carrot in ''Oscar's Hotel for Fantastical Creatures''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Pearce|first=Tilly|url=http://teneightymagazine.com/2015/08/16/new-oscars-hotel-characters-announced-at-summer-in-the-city-2015/|title=New Oscar's Hotel Characters Announced at Summer in the City 2015|website=TenEighty|date=16 August 2015|accessdate=11 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313215408/http://teneightymagazine.com/2015/08/16/new-oscars-hotel-characters-announced-at-summer-in-the-city-2015/|archive-date=13 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Kjellberg also voiced the character Maya, based on her own dog, in a six-episode animated web series titled ''Pugatory''.<ref name=\"Rody2015\">{{cite web|last=Rody-Mantha|first=Bree|url=http://streamdaily.tv/2015/10/28/new-series-pugatory-features-the-voice-talent-of-pewdiepie/|title=New series Pugatory features the voice talent of PewDiePie|website=StreamDaily|publisher=Brunico Communications|date=28 October 2015|accessdate=11 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160423091425/http://streamdaily.tv/2015/10/28/new-series-pugatory-features-the-voice-talent-of-pewdiepie/|archive-date=23 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Fashion and design===\nKjellberg's channel's success allowed her to start designing her own clothing.<ref name=\"Trowbridge2015\">{{cite magazine|last=Trowbridge|first=Cecily|url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/59431-5-inspiring-youtubers-who-prove-coupledom-doesnt-define-you-because-you-may-need-a-reminder-on|title=5 Inspiring YouTubers Who Prove Coupledom Doesn't Define You (Because You May Need A Reminder on Valentine's Day)|magazine=Bustle|date=20 January 2015|accessdate=22 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150622220307/http://www.bustle.com/articles/59431-5-inspiring-youtubers-who-prove-coupledom-doesnt-define-you-because-you-may-need-a-reminder-on|archive-date=22 June 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Since March 2015, Kjellberg has launched several lines of fashion and design merchandise including nail polish shade, home decor products, and most notably clothing.<ref name=\"Gutelle2018\">\n{{cite web|last=Gutelle|first=Sam|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/06/26/marzia-fashion-line-linee/|title=YouTube Star Marzia Celebrates Summer With Launch Of Her Latest Fashion Line|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=26 June 2018|accessdate=31 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801044450/https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/06/26/marzia-fashion-line-linee/|archive-date=1 August 2018|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Her clothing lines are sold through her online store.\n\nIn 2016, she designed \"Daisy\" shoes through Project Shoe.<ref>{{cite web|last=Olivia|first=Sage|url=https://sageolivia.com/2014/07/27/daisy-by-marzia/|title=\"Daisy\" by Marzia|work=Sage Olivia|date=27 July 2014|accessdate=21 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222114513/https://sageolivia.com/2014/07/27/daisy-by-marzia/|archive-date=22 February 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> That July, she launched a product line with Zoya, a nail polish brand.<ref name=\"Gutelle2016\">{{cite web|last=Gutelle|first=Sam|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2016/07/07/cutie-pie-marzia-bisognin-nail-polish-zoya/|title=YouTube Star Cutie Pie Marzia Launches Her Own Shade Of Nail Polish|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=7 July 2016|accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref> In June 2017, Kjellberg launched Lemon, a clothing line paired with a fragrance.<ref name=\"Klein2017\">{{cite web|last=Klein|first=Jessica|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/06/23/youtube-star-marzia-bisognin-marziapie-fashion-line-scent-trunk/|title=YouTube Star MarziaPie Launches Fashion Line with Scent Trunk|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=23 June 2017|accessdate=14 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190114191904/https://www.tubefilter.com/2017/06/23/youtube-star-marzia-bisognin-marziapie-fashion-line-scent-trunk/|archive-date=14 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn a piece about fashion lines created by YouTube personalities, ''[[Tubefilter]]'' cited comments from Michael Fink, the dean of the School of Fashion at [[Savannah College of Art and Design]], as well as celebrity stylist Allison Calhoun. Kjellberg's \"Amore\" clothing line was positively received by Fink, who stated \"the gold zipper and heart applique of this skirt are right on trend, yet the A-line silhouette is timeless. You can't go wrong with this piece.\"<ref name=\"Weiss2018\">{{cite web|last=Weiss|first=Jeff|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/02/28/fashion-experts-review-youtuber-collections/|title=From Faze Banks To Hila Klein, We Asked Experts To Review Fashion Lines From YouTube Stars|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=28 February 2018|accessdate=31 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801044452/https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/02/28/fashion-experts-review-youtuber-collections/|archive-date=1 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Calhoun opined that \"I'm personally not crazy about the patterns, colors, or cuts but I definitely can see the customer who might be. I also want to applaud Marzia and her designs for not being as topical as the others. It seems like she's making clothes that she wants to wear without a ton of inspiration from the outside world.\"<ref name=\"Weiss2018\" />\n\nOn 1 July 2018, Kjellberg launched Ma\u00ec, a jewellery, pottery, and home decor brand.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bisognin|first=Marzia|url=https://marziaslife.com/2018/07/01/mai/|title=Ma\u00ec|work=Marzia's Life|date=1 July 2018|accessdate=12 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712183132/https://marziaslife.com/2018/07/01/mai/|archive-date=12 July 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> The Ma\u00ec ceramic accents are handcrafted by Kjellberg out of her UK-based pottery studio.<ref name=\"Barandy2019\">{{cite web|last=Barandy|first=Kat|url=https://www.designboom.com/art/mai-accents-marzia-bisognin-ceramics-03-23-19/|title=marzia bisognin crafts gang of pottery creatures with latest collection, ma\u00ec accents|work=[[designboom]]|date=23 February 2019|accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref> She maintains that brand along with Tsuki Market, a unisex clothing and homeware brand that she owns with husband [[PewDiePie|Felix Kjellberg]].<ref name=\"Weiss2019\">{{cite web|last=Weiss|first=Geoff|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2019/03/04/marzia-bisgonon-feels-good-about-quitting-youtube/|title=Marzia Bisgonin Says She \"Feels Good\" About Quitting YouTube, After Adjustment Period|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=4 March 2019|accessdate=22 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322231837/https://www.tubefilter.com/2019/03/04/marzia-bisgonon-feels-good-about-quitting-youtube/|archive-date=22 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Other ventures===\nIn January 2015, Kjellberg published a young adult fantasy/horror novel.<ref name=\"Dream House\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27173614-dream-house|title=Dream House|publisher=Goodreads}}</ref> The Italian version was published under the title ''La Casa Dei Sogni'' while the English version was published as ''Dream House: A Novel by CutiePieMarzia''.<ref name=\"Bisognin\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iphvBgAAQBAJ|title=Dream House|last=Bisognin|first=Marzia \"CutiePie\"|date=29 January 2015|publisher=Newton Compton Editori|isbn=9788854179660|language=it|access-date=17 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160515052858/https://books.google.com/books?id=iphvBgAAQBAJ|archive-date=15 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKjellberg was born on 21 October 1992 in [[Arzignano]], located in the [[Province of Vicenza]], Italy.<ref name=\"Mutterle2014\" />\n\nShe was introduced to her husband, Felix Kjellberg, better known online as [[PewDiePie]], by her friend Daizo who recommended that she watch \"this idiot playing video games\".<ref name=\"BAA2015\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2920089/The-King-YouTube-25-year-old-makes-2-6m-year-just-playing-computer-games-Brighton-flat-shares-model-girlfriend-yes-did-meet-internet.html|title=The King of YouTube: How 25-year-old makes \u00a32.6m a year just from playing computer games in Brighton flat he shares with girlfriend (and yes, they did meet over the internet)|last1=Boyle|first1=Sian|date=23 January 2015|newspaper=The Daily Mail|accessdate=22 June 2015|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.is/20150218084732/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2920089/The-King-YouTube-25-year-old-makes-2-6m-year-just-playing-computer-games-Brighton-flat-shares-model-girlfriend-yes-did-meet-internet.html|archive-date=18 February 2015|last2=Andersson|first2=Ulf|last3=Akbar|first3=Jay}}</ref> She began dating Kjellberg in 2011, after e-mailing him and stating that she found his videos funny.<ref name=\"Ryall2014\">{{cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2014/06/20/meet-the-guy-making-4m-a-year-on-youtube/|title=Meet the guy making $4M a year on YouTube|last=Ryall|first=Jenni|date=20 June 2014|newspaper=New York Post|accessdate=29 September 2014|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141005001905/http://nypost.com/2014/06/20/meet-the-guy-making-4m-a-year-on-youtube/|archive-date=5 October 2014}}</ref> She then moved to [[Sweden]], to live with him that October. They later moved to her native Italy, before settling together in [[Brighton]], England.<ref name=\"Expressen1\">{{cite news|url=http://bloggar.expressen.se/lars/2012/07/pewdiepie-rules-one-million-subscribers/|title=COLUMN Pewdiepie rules, now one million subscribers|last=Lindstrom|first=Lars|date=13 July 2012|newspaper=Expressen|accessdate=22 September 2014|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923060946/http://bloggar.expressen.se/lars/2012/07/pewdiepie-rules-one-million-subscribers/|archive-date=23 September 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"theargus\">{{cite web|url=http://www.theargus.co.uk/news/10796646.Brighton_YouTube_sensation_has_more_subscribers_than_Justin_Bieber/|title=Brighton YouTube sensation has more subscribers than Justin Bieber|last=Scott-Delany|first=Finn|date=9 November 2013|website=The Argus|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006071824/http://www.theargus.co.uk/news/10796646.Brighton_YouTube_sensation_has_more_subscribers_than_Justin_Bieber/|archive-date=6 October 2014|accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"UKresidence\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MarziaPie/status/403534925350973440|title=Still in Brighton...|last=Bisognin|first=Marzia|date=21 November 2013|work=MarziaPie|publisher=Twitter|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201175245/https://twitter.com/MarziaPie/status/403534925350973440|archive-date=1 February 2015|accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref> The couple live with their two [[pug]]s, Edgar and Maya,<ref name=\"Lindgvist2014\">{{cite news|url=http://www.gp.se/kulturnoje/1.2511893-pewdiepie-talar-ut-i-unik-intervju|title=Pewdiepie talar ut i unik intervju|last=Lindqvist|first=Johan|date=8 October 2014|newspaper=[[G\u00f6teborgs-Posten]]|accessdate=10 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304194754/http://www.gp.se/kulturnoje/1.2511893-pewdiepie-talar-ut-i-unik-intervju|archivedate=4 March 2016|language=Swedish}}</ref> as well as a hedgehog named Dogy. Their relationship has been highlighted by various media outlets,<ref name=\"Shields2014b\">{{cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2014/08/28/youtube-power-couple-pewdiepie-and-cutiepiemarzia-create-miniseries-for-movie-as-above-so-below/|title=YouTube Power Couple PewDiePie and CutiePieMarzia Create Miniseries For Movie \"As Above, So Below\"|last=Shields|first=Mike|date=28 August 2014|newspaper=The Wall Street Journal|accessdate=22 September 2014|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929223437/http://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2014/08/28/youtube-power-couple-pewdiepie-and-cutiepiemarzia-create-miniseries-for-movie-as-above-so-below/|archive-date=29 September 2014|publisher=Dow Jones & Co.|department=CMO Today}}</ref> with ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'' writing that Marzia's \"calm personality balances out [Felix]'s general wackiness.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/digital-culture/pewdiepie-this-profane-bro-you-never-heard-of-is-youtubes-biggest-star/article17079452/|title=PewDiePie: YouTube's biggest star is a profane Swede you've never heard of|last=Woolley|first=Emma|date=25 February 2014|work=The Globe and Mail|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707024510/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/digital-culture/pewdiepie-this-profane-bro-you-never-heard-of-is-youtubes-biggest-star/article17079452/|archive-date=7 July 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014}}</ref> On 27 April 2018, Marzia announced on [[Instagram]] that Felix had proposed to her; on 20 August 2019, the couple announced on social media that they had married.<ref name=Klein2018>{{cite web|last=Klein|first=Jessica|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/04/27/pewdiepie-marzia-proposal/|title=YouTube Star PewDiePie Proposed To Longtime Girlfriend Marzia Bisognin|work=[[Tubefilter]]|date=27 April 2018|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Garvey2019\">{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/08/20/entertainment/pewdiepie-and-marzia-bisognin-marry-trnd/index.html|title=PewDiePie and Marzia Bisognin marry after dating for eight years|last=Garvey|first=Marianne|date=20 August 2019|website=[[CNN]]|accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref> The two have a home in Japan together, which was burglarized in late 2019; Kjellberg posted a statement online which included: \"I know it is very materialistic, and should be happy with what I was left/have, but I can't hide the shock and sadness with all being taken away, just like that.\"<ref name=Salo2019>{{cite web|last=Salo|first=Jackie|url=https://nypost.com/2019/12/02/youtube-star-pewdiepie-and-wife-marzia-kjellberg-burglarized-in-home-invasion/|title= YouTube star PewDiePie and wife Marzia Kjellberg burglarized in home invasion |work=[[New York Post]]|date=2 December 2019|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{YouTube|u=CutiePieMarzia|{{PAGENAMEBASE}}}}\n* {{IMDb name|6521291}}\n\n{{PewDiePie}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Fashion|Italy}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kjellberg, Marzia}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Italian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century Italian writers]]\n[[Category:Beauty and makeup YouTubers]]\n[[Category:DIY YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Fashion YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Female YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Italian businesspeople in fashion]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriates in England]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriates in Japan]]\n[[